# Logging Privacy (Rust)

## What to log — tool name, duration, errors only
Use the helpers in `src-core/instrument-desktop/src/command_log.rs`:
- `command_log::finish_ok(tool_name, start)` — for infallible commands
- `command_log::finish_result(tool_name, start, &result)` — for Result-returning commands

## What NEVER to log
**Never** log input values, output values, or any field content the user typed.
This is a hard privacy requirement — not a style preference.

Bad:
```rust
log::debug!("base64 input: {}", input.value);  // ❌ logs user content
```

Good:
```rust
command_log::finish_ok("base64_process", start);  // ✅ logs name + duration only
```

## Fast completions are intentionally silent
Calls completing in <200ms produce no log entry. This is by design — auto-run tools
fire on every keystroke and would flood the log file with noise.
Only slow calls (WARN) and errors (ERROR) are persisted to the log file.
